        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>PART II.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2>OF SEXUAL UNION.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER I.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>KINDS OF SEXUAL UNION ACCORDING TO</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><span class=\"c5\">(<i>a</i>) DIMENSIONS.<br></span> <span class=\"c5\">(<i>b</i>) FORCE OF DESIRE OR PASSION.<br></span> <span class=\"c5\">(<i>c</i>) TIME.</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"center\"><i>Kinds of Union.</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Man is divided into three classes, viz., the hare man, the bull man, and the horse man, according to the size of his lingam.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Woman also, according to the depth of her yoni, is either a female deer, a mare, or a female elephant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are thus three equal unions between persons of corresponding dimensions, and there are six unequal unions, when the dimensions do not correspond, or nine in all, as the following table shows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\"><table class=\"c7\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" class=\"tdsc c6\">EQUAL.</td>\n<td colspan=\"2\" class=\"tdsc c6\">UNEQUAL.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbr19 c6\">Men.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbr19 c6\">Women.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbr19 c6\">Men.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbr19 c6\">Women</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Hare.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Deer.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Hare.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Mare.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Bull.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Mare.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Hare.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Elephant.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Horse.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Elephant.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Bull.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Deer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Bull.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Elephant.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Horse.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Deer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Horse.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Mare.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>In these unequal unions, when the male exceeds the female in point of size, his union with a woman who is immediately next to him in size is called high union, and is of two kinds; while his union with the woman most remote from him in size is called the <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002476\">highest</$link> union, and is of one kind only. On the other hand when the female exceeds the male in point of size, her union with a man immediately next to her in size is called low union, and is of two kinds; while her union with a man most remote from her in size is called the lowest union, and is of one kind only.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In other words, the horse and mare, the bull and deer, form the high union, while the horse and deer form the highest union. On the female side, the elephant and bull, the mare and hare, form low unions, while the elephant and the hare make the lowest unions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are then, nine kinds of union according to dimensions. Amongst all these, equal unions are the best, those of a superlative degree, <i>i.e.</i>, the highest and the lowest, are the worst, and the rest are middling, and with them the high<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002250\">[33]</$link> are better than the low.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also nine kinds of union according to the force of passion or carnal desire, as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\"><table class=\"c8\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"tcb6\">Men.</td>\n<td class=\"tcb6\">Women.</td>\n<td class=\"tcb6\">Men.</td>\n<td class=\"tcb6\">Women</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Small.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\"> </td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Intense.</td>\n<td class=\"tlbrl9\">Middling.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"centered\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>A man is called a man of small passion whose desire at the time of sexual union is not great, whose semen is scanty, and who cannot bear the warm embraces of the female.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Those who differ from this temperament are called men of middling passion, while those of intense passion are full of desire.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the same way, women are supposed to have the three degrees of feeling as specified above.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Lastly, according to time there are three kinds of men and women, viz., the short-timed, the moderate-timed, and the long-timed, and of these as in the previous statements, there are nine kinds of union.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>But on this last head there is a difference of opinion about the female, which should be stated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Auddalika says, &quot;Females do not emit as males do. The males simply remove their desire, while the females, from their consciousness of desire, feel a certain kind of pleasure, which gives them satisfaction, but it is impossible for them to tell you what kind of pleasure they feel. The fact from which this becomes evident is, that males, when engaged in coition, cease of themselves after emission, and are satisfied, but it is not so with females.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This opinion is, however, objected to on the grounds that if a male be a long-timed, the female loves him the more, but if he be short-timed, she is dissatisfied with him. And this circumstance, some say, would prove that the female emits also.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>But this opinion does not hold good, for if it takes a long time to allay a woman's desire, and during this time she is enjoying great pleasure, it is quite natural then that she should wish for its continuation. And on this subject there is a verse as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;By union with men the lust, desire, or passion of women is satisfied, and the pleasure derived from the consciousness of it is called their satisfaction.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The followers of Babhravya, however, say that the semen of women continues to fall from the beginning of the sexual union to its end, and it is right that it should be so, for if they had no semen there would be no embryo.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>To this there is an objection. In the beginning of coition the passion of the woman is middling, and she cannot bear<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> the vigorous thrusts of her lover, but by degrees her passion increases until she ceases to think about her body, and then finally she wishes to stop from further coition.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This objection, however, does not hold good, for even in ordinary things that revolve with great force, such as a potter's wheel, or a top, we find that the motion at first is slow, but by degrees it becomes very rapid. In the same way the passion of the woman having gradually increased, she has a desire to discontinue coition, when all the semen has fallen away. And there is a verse with regard to this as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;The fall of the semen of the man takes place only at the end of coition, while the semen of the woman falls continually, and after the semen of both has all fallen away then they wish for the discontinuance of coition.&quot;<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002254\">[34]</$link></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Lastly, Vatsyayana is of opinion that the semen of the female falls in the same way as that of the male.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now some may ask here: If men and women are beings of the same kind, and are engaged in bringing about the same result, why should they have different works to do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Vatsya says that this is so, because the ways of working as well as the consciousness of pleasure in men and women are different. The difference in the ways of working, by which men are the actors, and women are the persons acted upon, is owing to the nature of the male and the female, otherwise the actor would be sometimes the person acted upon, and vice versâ. And from this difference in the ways of working follows the difference in the consciousness of pleasure, for a man thinks, &quot;this woman is united with me,&quot; and a woman thinks, &quot;I am united with this man.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>It may be said that if <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002478\">the</$link> ways of working in men and women are different, why should not there be a difference, even in the pleasure they feel, and which is the result of those ways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>But this objection is groundless, for the person acting and<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> the person acted upon being of different kinds, there is a reason for the difference in their ways of working; but there is no reason for any difference in the pleasure they feel, because they both naturally derive pleasure from the act they perform.<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002258\">[35]</$link></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>On this again some may say that when different persons are engaged in doing the same work, we find that they accomplish the same end or purpose: while, on the contrary, in the case of men and women we find that each of them accomplishes his or her own end separately, and this is inconsistent. But this is a mistake, for we find that sometimes two things are done at the same time, as for instance in the fighting of rams, both the rams receive the shock at the same time on their heads. Again, in throwing one wood apple against another, and also in a fight or struggle of wrestlers. If it be said that in these cases the things employed are of the same kind, it is answered that even in the case of men and women, the nature of the two persons is the same. And as the difference in their ways of working arises from the difference of their conformation only, it follows that men experience the same kind of pleasure as women do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There is also a verse on this subject as follows: &quot;Men and women being of the same nature, feel the same kind of pleasure, and therefore a man should marry such a woman as will love him ever afterwards.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The pleasure of men and women being thus proved to be of the same kind, it follows that in regard to time, there are nine kinds of sexual intercourse, in the same way as there are nine kinds, according to the force of passion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There being thus nine kinds of union with regard to dimensions, force of passion, and time, respectively, by making<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> combinations of them, innumerable kinds of union would be produced. Therefore in each particular kind of sexual union, men should use such means as they may think suitable for the occasion.<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002262\">[36]</$link></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>At the first time of sexual union the passion of the male is intense, and his time is short, but in subsequent unions on the same day the reverse of this is the case. With the female, however, it is the contrary, for at the first time her passion is weak, and then her time long, but on subsequent occasions on the same day, her passion is intense and her time short, until her passion is satisfied.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"center\"><i>On the different kinds of Love.</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Men learned in the humanities are of opinion that love is of four kinds, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"1\">Love acquired by continual habit.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"2\">Love resulting from the imagination.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"3\">Love resulting from belief.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"4\">Love resulting from the perception of external objects.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(1). Love resulting from the constant and continual performance and habit, as for instance the love of sexual intercourse, the love of hunting, the love of drinking, the love of gambling, etc., etc.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(2). Love which is felt for things to which we are not habituated, and which proceeds entirely from ideas, is called love resulting from imagination, as for instance, that love which some men and women and eunuchs feel for the Auparishtaka or mouth congress, and that which is felt by all for such things as embracing, kissing, etc., etc.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(3). The love which is mutual on both sides, and proved to be true, when each looks upon the other as his or her very own, such is called love resulting from belief by the learned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(4). The love resulting from the perception of eternal<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> objects is quite evident and well-known to the world, because the pleasure which it affords is superior to the pleasure of the other kinds of love, which exists only for its sake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>What has been said in this chapter upon the subject of sexual union is sufficient for the learned; but for the edification of the ignorant, the same will now be treated of at length and in detail.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER II.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF THE EMBRACE.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This part of the Kama Shastra, which treats of sexual union, is also called &quot;Sixty-four&quot; (Chatushshashti). Some old authors say that it is called so, because it contains sixty-four chapters. Others are of opinion that the author of this part being a person named Panchala, and the person who recited the part of the Rig Veda called Dashatapa, which contains sixty-four verses, being also called Panchala, the name &quot;sixty-four&quot; has been given to the part of the work in honour of the Rig Vedas. The followers of Babhravya say on the other hand that this part contains eight subjects, viz., the embrace, kissing, scratching with the nails or fingers, biting, lying down, making various sounds, playing the part of a man, and the Auparishtaka, or mouth congress. Each of these subjects being of eight kinds, and eight multiplied by eight being sixty-four, this part is therefore named &quot;sixty-four.&quot; But Vatsyayana affirms that as this part contains also the following subjects, viz., striking, crying, the acts of a man during congress, the various kinds of congress, and other subjects, the name &quot;sixty-four&quot; is given to it only accidentally. As, for instance, we say this tree is &quot;Saptaparna,&quot; or seven-leaved, this offering of rice is &quot;Panchavarna,&quot; or five-coloured, but the tree has not seven leaves, neither has the rice <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002480\">five</$link> colours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>However the part sixty-four is now treated of, and the embrace, being the first subject, will now be considered.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now the embrace which indicates the mutual love of a man and woman who have come together is of four kinds, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000571": {
            "role": "text",
