            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"4\"><i>Kshiraniraka</i>, or milk and water embrace.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(1). When a woman, clinging to a man as a creeper twines round a tree, bends his head down to hers with the desire of kissing him and slightly makes the sound of sut sut, embraces him, and looks lovingly towards him, it is called an embrace like the &quot;twining of a creeper.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(2). When a woman, having placed one of her feet on the foot of her lover, and the other on one of his thighs, passes one of her arms round his back, and the other on his shoulders, makes slightly the sounds of singing and cooing, and wishes, as it were, to climb up him in order to have a kiss, it is called an embrace like the &quot;climbing of a tree.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>These two kinds of embrace take place when the lover is standing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(3). When lovers lie on a bed, and embrace each other so<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> closely that the arms and thighs of the one are encircled by the arms and thighs of the other, and are, as it were, rubbing up against them, this is called an embrace like &quot;the mixture of sesamum seed with rice.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(4). When a man and a woman are very much in love with each other, and not thinking of any pain or hurt, embrace each other as if they were entering into each other's bodies, either while the woman is sitting on the lap of the man or in front of him, or on a bed, then it is called an embrace like a &quot;mixture of milk and water.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>These two kinds of embrace take place at the time of sexual union.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Babhravya has thus related to us the above eight kinds of embraces.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Suvarnanabha, moreover, gives us four ways of embracing simple members of the body, which are:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000606",
