            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(2). When, covering the end of the lingam with his fingers collected together like the bud of a plant or flower, the eunuch presses the sides of it with his lips, using his teeth also, it is called &quot;biting the sides.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(3). When, being desired to proceed, the eunuch presses the end of the lingam with his lips closed together, and kisses it as if he were drawing it out, it is called the &quot;outside pressing.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(4). When, being asked to go on, he put the lingam further into his mouth, and presses it with his lips and then takes it out, it is called the &quot;inside pressing.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(5). When, holding the lingam in his hand, the eunuch kisses it as if he were kissing the lower lip, it is called &quot;kissing.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(6). When, after kissing it, he touches it with his tongue everywhere, and passes the tongue <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002492\">over</$link> the end of it, it is called &quot;rubbing.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(7). When, in the same way, he puts the half of it into his mouth, and forcibly kisses and sucks it, this is called &quot;sucking a mangoe fruit.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(8). And lastly, when, with the consent of the man, the eunuch puts the whole lingam into his mouth, and presses it to the very end, as if he were going to swallow it up, it is called &quot;swallowing up.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Striking, scratching, and other things may also be done during this kind of congress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>The Auparishtaka is practised only by unchaste and wanton women, female attendants and serving maids, <i>i.e.</i>, those who are not married to anybody, but who live by shampooing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The Acharyas (<i>i.e.</i>, ancient and venerable authors) are of opinion that this Auparishtaka is the work of a dog and not of a man, because it is a low practice, and opposed to the orders of the Holy Writ, and because the man himself suffers by bringing his lingam into contact with the mouths of eunuchs and women. But Vatsyayana says that the orders of the Holy Writ do not affect those who resort to courtezans, and the law prohibits the practice of the Auparishtaka with married women only. As regards the injury to the male, that can be easily remedied.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The people of Eastern India do not resort to women who practise the Auparishtaka.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The people of Ahichhatra resort to such women, but do nothing with them, so far as the mouth is concerned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The people of Saketa do with these women every kind of mouth congress, while the people of Nagara do not practise this, but do every other thing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The people of the Shurasena country, on the <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002494\">southern</$link> bank of the Jumna, do everything without any hesitation, for they say that women being naturally unclean, no one can be certain about their character, their purity, their conduct, their practices, their confidences, or their speech. They are not however on this account to be abandoned, because religious law, on the authority of which they are reckoned pure, lays down that the udder of a cow is clean at the time of milking, though the mouth of a cow, and also the mouth of her calf, are considered unclean by the Hindoos. Again a dog is clean when he seizes a deer in hunting, though food touched by a dog is otherwise considered very unclean. A bird is clean when it causes a fruit to fall from a tree by pecking at it, though things eaten by crows and other birds are considered unclean. And the mouth of a woman is clean for kissing and such like things at the time of sexual intercourse. Vatsyayana moreover thinks that in all these things connected with love, everybody should act according to the custom of his country, and his own inclination.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also the following verses on the subject.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;The male servants of some men carry on the mouth congress with their masters. It is also practised by some citizens,<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> who know each other well, among themselves. Some women of the harem, when they are amorous, do the acts of the mouth on the yonis of one another, and some men do the same thing with women. The way of doing this (<i>i.e.</i>, of kissing the yoni) should be known from kissing the mouth. When a man and woman lie down in an inverted order, <i>i.e.</i>, with the head of the one towards the feet of the other and carry on this congress, it is called the &quot;congress of a crow.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>For the sake of such things courtezans abandon men possessed of good qualities, liberal and clever, and become attached to low persons, such as slaves and elephant drivers. The Auparishtaka, or mouth congress, should never be done by a learned Brahman, by a minister that carries on the business of a state, or by a man of good reputation, because though the practice is allowed by the Shastras, there is no reason why it should be carried on, and need only be practised in particular cases. As for instance, the taste, and the strength, and the digestive qualities of the flesh of dogs are mentioned in works on medicine, but it does not therefore follow that it should be eaten by the wise. In the same way there are some men, some places and some times, with respect to which these practices can be made <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002496\">use</$link> of. A man should therefore pay regard to the place, to the time, and to the practice which is to be carried out, as also as to whether it is agreeable to his nature and to himself, and then he may or may not practise these things according to circumstances. But after all, these things being done secretly, and the mind of the man being fickle, how can it be known what any person will do at any particular time and for any particular purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER X.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF THE WAY HOW TO BEGIN AND HOW TO END THE CONGRESS.<br>\n<br>\nDIFFERENT KINDS OF CONGRESS AND LOVE QUARRELS.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the pleasure-room, decorated with flowers, and fragrant with perfumes, attended by his friends and servants, the citizen should receive the woman, who will come bathed and dressed, and will invite her to take refreshment and to drink freely. He should then seat her on his left side, and holding her hair, and touching also the end and knot of her garment, he should gently embrace her with his right arm. They should then carry on an amusing conversation on various subjects, and may also talk suggestively of things which would be considered as coarse, or not to be mentioned generally in society. They may then sing, either with or without gesticulations, and play on musical instruments, talk about the arts, and persuade each other to drink. At last when the woman is overcome with love and desire, the citizen should dismiss the people that may be with him, giving them flowers, ointment, and betel leaves, and then when the two are left alone, they should proceed as has been already described in the previous chapters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Such is the beginning of sexual union. At the end of the congress, the lovers with modesty, and not looking at each other, should go separately to the washing-room. After this, sitting in their own places, they should eat some betel leaves, and the citizen should apply with his own hand to the body of the woman some pure sandal wood ointment, or ointment of some other kind. He should then embrace her with his left arm, and with agreeable words should cause her to drink from a cup held in his own hand, or he may give her water to drink. They can then eat <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002498\">sweetmeats</$link>, or anything else, according to their likings, and may drink fresh juice,<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002278\">[40]</$link> soup, gruel, extracts of meat, sherbet, the juice of<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> mangoe fruits, the extract of the juice of the citron tree mixed with sugar, or anything that may be liked in different countries, and known to be sweet, soft, and pure. The lovers may also sit on the terrace of the palace or house, and enjoy the moonlight, and carry on an agreeable conversation. At this time, too, while the woman lies in his lap, with her face towards the moon, the citizen should show her the different planets, the morning star, the polar star, and the seven Rishis, or Great Bear.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This is the end of sexual union.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Congress is of the following kinds, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000980",
