        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"7\">Congress of spontaneous love.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(1). When a man and a woman, who have been in love with each other for some time, come together with great difficulty, or when one of the two returns from a journey, or is reconciled after having been separated on account of a quarrel, then congress is called the &quot;loving congress.&quot; It is carried on according to the liking of the lovers, and as long as they choose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(2). When two persons come together, while their love for each other is still in its infancy, their congress is called the &quot;congress of subsequent love.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(3). When a man carries on the congress by exciting himself by means of the sixty-four ways, such as kissing, etc., etc., or when a man and a woman come together, though in reality they are both attached to different persons, their congress is then called &quot;congress of artificial love.&quot; At this time all the ways and means mentioned in the Kama Shastra should be used.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(4). When a man, from the beginning to the end of the congress,<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> though having connection with the women, thinks all the time that he is enjoying another one whom he loves, it is called the &quot;congress of transferred love.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(5). Congress between a man and a female water carrier, or a female servant of a caste lower than his own, lasting only until the desire is satisfied, is called &quot;congress like that of eunuchs.&quot; Here external touches, kisses, and manipulations are not to be employed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(6). The congress between a courtezan and a rustic, and that between citizens and the women of villages, and bordering countries, is called, &quot;deceitful congress.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(7). The congress that takes place between two persons who are attached to one another, and which is done according to their own liking is called &quot;spontaneous congress.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus ends the kinds of congress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>We shall now speak of love quarrels.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A woman who is very much in love with a man cannot bear to hear the name of her rival mentioned, or to have any conversation regarding her, or to be addressed by her name through mistake. If such takes place, a great quarrel arises, and the woman cries, becomes angry, tosses her hair about, strikes her lover, falls from her bed or seat, and, casting aside her garlands and ornaments, throws herself down on the ground.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>At this time, the lover should attempt to reconcile her with conciliatory words, and should take her up carefully and place her on her bed. But she, not replying to his questions, and with increased anger, should bend down his head by pulling his hair, and having kicked him once, twice, or thrice on his arms, head, bosom or back, should then proceed to the door of the room. Dattaka says that she should then sit angrily near the door and shed tears, but should not go out, because she would be found fault with for going away. After a time, when she thinks that the conciliatory words and actions of her lover have reached their utmost, she should then embrace him, talking to him with harsh and reproachful words, but at the same time showing a loving desire for congress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When the woman is in her own house, and has quarrelled with her lover, she should go to him and show how angry she is, and leave him. Afterwards the citizen having sent the<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> Vita,<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002282\">[41]</$link> the Vidushaka<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002282\">[41]</$link> or the Pithamurda<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002282\">[41]</$link> to pacify her, she should accompany them back to the house, and spend the night with her lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the love quarrels.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In conclusion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A man, employing the sixty-four means mentioned by Babhravya, obtains his object, and enjoys the woman of the first quality. Though he may speak well on other subjects, if he does not know the sixty-four divisions, no great respect is paid to him in the assembly of the learned. A man, devoid of other knowledge, but well acquainted with the sixty-four divisions, becomes a leader in any society of men and women. What man will not respect the sixty-four parts,<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002286\">[42]</$link> considering they are respected by the learned, by the cunning, and by the courtezans. As the sixty-four parts are respected, are charming, and add to the talent of women, they are called by the Acharyas dear to women. A man skilled in the sixty-four parts is looked upon with love by his own wife, by the wives of others, and by courtezans.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"fm3\"><span class=\"smcap c10\"><a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002500\">End of Part II</$link>.</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>PART III.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2>ABOUT THE ACQUISITION OF A WIFE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER I.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>ON MARRIAGE.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a girl of the same caste, and a virgin, is married in accordance with the precepts of Holy Writ, the results of such an union are: the acquisition of Dharma and Artha, offspring, affinity, increase of friends, and untarnished love. For this reason a man should fix his affections upon a girl who is of good family, whose parents are alive, and who is three years or more younger than himself. She should be born of a highly respectable family, possessed of wealth, well connected, and with many relations and friends. She should also be beautiful, of a good disposition, with lucky marks on her body, and with good hair, nails, teeth, ears, eyes, and breasts, neither more nor less than they ought to be, and no one of them entirely wanting, and not troubled with a sickly body. The man should, of course, also possess these qualities himself. But at all events, says Ghotakamukha, a girl who has been already joined with others (<i>i.e.</i>, no longer a maiden) should never be loved, for it would be reproachable to do such a thing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now in order to bring about a marriage with such a girl as described above, the parents and relations of the man should exert themselves, as also such friends on both sides as may be desired to assist in the matter. These friends should bring to the notice of the girl's parents, the faults, both present and future, of all the other men that may wish to marry her, and<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> should at the same time extol even to exaggeration all the excellencies, ancestral, and paternal, of their friend, so as to endear him to them, and particularly to those that may be liked by the girl's mother. One of the friends should also disguise himself as an astrologer and declare the future good fortune and wealth of his friend by showing the existence of all the lucky omens<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002290\">[43]</$link> and signs,<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002294\">[44]</$link> the good influence of planets, the auspicious entrance of the sun into a sign of the Zodiac, propitious stars and fortunate marks on his body. Others again should rouse the jealousy of the girl's mother by telling her that their friend has a chance of getting from some other quarter even a better girl than hers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A girl should be taken as a wife, as also given in marriage, when fortune, signs, omens, and the words<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002298\">[45]</$link> of others are favourable, for, says Ghotakamukha, a man should not marry at any time he likes. A girl who is asleep, crying, or gone out of the house when sought in marriage, or who is betrothed to another, should not be married. The following also should be avoided:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"1\">One who is kept concealed.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"2\">One who has an ill-sounding name.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"3\">One who has her nose depressed.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"4\">One who has her nostril turned up.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"5\">One who is formed like a male.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001032",
