        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"9\">The jealousy of her husband.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also the following verses on the subject.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;A clever man, learning from the Shastras the ways of winning over the wives of other people, is never deceived in the case of his own wives. No one, however, should make use of these ways for <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002526\">seducing</$link> the wives of others, because they do not always succeed, and, moreover, often cause disasters, and the destruction of Dharma and Artha. This book, which is intended for the good of the people, and to teach them the ways of guarding their own wives, should not be made use of merely for gaining over the wives of others.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"fm3\"><span class=\"smcap c10\">End of Part V.</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>PART VI.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2>ABOUT COURTESANS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>INTRODUCTORY REMARKS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This Part VI., about courtesans, was prepared by Vatsyayana, from a treatise on the subject, that was written by Dattaka, for the women of Pataliputra (the modern Patna), some two thousand years ago. Dattaka's work does not appear to be extant now, but this abridgement of it is very clever, and quite equal to any of the productions of Emile Zola, and other writers of the realistic school of to-day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Although a great deal has been written on the subject of the courtesan, nowhere will be found a better description of her, of her belongings, of her ideas, and of the working of her mind, than is contained in the following pages.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The details of the domestic and social life of the early Hindoos would not be complete without mention of the courtesan, and Part VI. is entirely devoted to this subject. The Hindoos have ever had the good sense to recognise courtesans as a part and portion of human society, and so long as they behaved themselves with decency and propriety, they were regarded with a certain respect. Anyhow, they have never been treated in the East with that brutality and contempt so common in the West, while their education has always been of a superior kind to that bestowed upon the rest of womankind in Oriental countries.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the earlier days the well-educated Hindoo dancing girl and courtesan doubtless resembled the Hetera of the Greeks, and being educated and amusing, were far more acceptable as companions than the generality of the married or unmarried women of that period. At all times and in all countries, there has ever been a little rivalry between the chaste and the unchaste. But while some women are born courtesans,<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> and follow the instincts of their nature in every class of society, it has been truly said by some authors that every woman has got an inkling of the profession in her nature, and does her best, as a general rule, to make herself agreeable to the male sex.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The subtlety of women, their wonderful perceptive powers, their knowledge, and their intuitive appreciation of men and things, are all shown in the following pages, which may be looked upon as a concentrated essence that has been since worked up into detail by many writers in every quarter of the globe.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER I.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF THE CAUSES OF A COURTESAN RESORTING TO MEN; OF THE MEANS OF ATTACHING TO HERSELF THE MAN DESIRED; AND OF THE KIND OF MAN THAT IT IS DESIRABLE TO BE ACQUAINTED WITH.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>By having intercourse with men courtesans obtain sexual pleasure, as well as their own <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002528\">maintenance</$link>. Now when a courtesan takes up with a man from love, the action is natural; but when she resorts to him for the purpose of getting money, her action is artificial or forced. Even in the latter case, however, she should conduct herself as if her love were indeed natural, because men repose their confidence on those women who apparently love them. In making known her love to the man she should show an entire freedom from avarice, and for the sake of her future credit she should abstain from acquiring money from him by unlawful means.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A courtesan, well dressed and wearing her ornaments, should sit or stand at the door of her house, and without exposing herself too much, should look on the public road so as to be seen by the passers by, she being like an object on view for sale.<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002420\">[74]</$link> She should form friendships with such persons as would enable her to separate men from other women, and attach<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> them to herself, and repair her own misfortunes, to acquire wealth, and to protect her from being bullied, or set upon by persons with whom she may have dealings of some kind or another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>These persons are:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"1\">The guards of the town, or the police.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001570",
