            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"18\">An ascetic who is internally troubled with desire.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"19\">A brave man.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"20\">A physician of the King.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"21\">Previous acquaintance.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>On the other hand, those who are possessed of excellent qualities are to be resorted to for the sake of love, and fame. Such men are as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Men of high birth, learned, with a good knowledge of the world, and doing the proper things at the proper times, poets, good story tellers, eloquent men, energetic men, skilled in various arts, far-seeing into the future, possessed of great minds, full of perseverance, of a firm devotion, free from anger, liberal, affectionate to their parents, and with a liking for all social gatherings, skilled in completing verses begun by others and in various other sports, free from all disease, possessed of a perfect body, strong, and not addicted to drinking, powerful in sexual enjoyment, sociable, showing love towards women and attracting their hearts to himself, but not entirely devoted to them, possessed of independent means of livelihood, free from envy, and last of all free from suspicion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Such are the good qualities of a man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The woman also should have the following characteristics, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>She should be possessed of beauty, and <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002530\">amiability</$link>, with auspicious body marks. She should have a liking for good qualities in other people, as also a liking for wealth. She should take delight in sexual unions resulting from love, and should be of a firm mind, and of the same class as the man with regard to sexual enjoyment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>She should always be anxious to acquire and obtain experience and knowledge, be free from avarice, and always have a liking for social gatherings, and for the arts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The following are the ordinary qualities of all women, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>To be possessed of intelligence, good disposition, and good manners; to be straightforward in behaviour, and to be grateful; to consider well the future before doing anything; to <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002532\">possess</$link> activity, to be of consistent behaviour, and to have a knowledge of the proper times and places for doing things;<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> to speak always without meanness, loud laughter, malignity, anger, avarice, dullness, or stupidity, to have a knowledge of the Kama Sutra, and to be skilled in all the arts connected with it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The faults of the women are to be known by the absence of any of the above mentioned good qualities.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The following kinds of men are not fit to be resorted to by courtesans, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>One who is consumptive; one who is sickly; one whose mouth contains worms; one whose breath smells like human excrement; one whose wife is dear to him; one who speaks harshly; one who is always suspicious; one who is avaricious; one who is pitiless; one who is a thief; one who is self-conceited; one who has a liking for sorcery; one who does not care for respect or disrespect; one who can be gained over even by his enemies by means of money; and lastly, one who is extremely bashful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Ancient authors are of opinion that the causes of a courtesan resorting to men are love, fear, money, pleasure, returning some act of enmity, curiosity, sorrow, constant intercourse, Dharma, celebrity, compassion, the desire of having a friend, shame, the likeness of the man to some beloved person, the search after good fortune, the getting rid of the love of somebody else, the being of the same class as the man with respect to sexual union, living in the same place, constancy, and poverty. But Vatsyayana decides that desire of wealth, freedom from misfortune, and love, are the only causes that affect the union of courtesans with men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now a courtesan should not sacrifice money to her love, because money is the chief thing to be attended to. But in cases of fear, etc., she should pay regard to strength and other qualities. Moreover, even though she be invited by any man to join him, she should not at once consent to an union, because men are apt to despise things which are easily acquired. On such occasions she should first send the shampooers, and the singers, and the jesters, who may be in her service, or, in their absence the Pithamardas, or confidants, and others, to find out the state of his feelings, and the condition of his mind. By means of these persons she should ascertain whether the man is pure or impure, affected, or the reverse, capable of attachment, or indifferent, liberal or niggardly; and if she finds him<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> to her liking, she should then employ the Vita and others to attach his mind to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Accordingly, the Pithamarda should bring the man to her house, under the pretence of seeing the fights of quails, cocks, and rams, of hearing the maina (a kind of starling) talk, or of seeing some other spectacle, or the practice of some art; or he may take the woman to the abode of the man. After this, when the man comes to her house the woman should give him something capable of producing curiosity, and love in his heart, such as an affectionate present, telling him that it was specially designed for his use. She should also amuse him for a long time by telling him such stories, and doing such things as he may take most delight in. When he goes away she should frequently send to him a female attendant, skilled in carrying on a jesting conversation, and also a small present at the same time. She should also sometimes go to him herself under the pretence of some business, and accompanied by the Pithamarda.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the means of attaching to herself the man desired.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also some verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;When a lover comes to her abode, a courtesan should give him a mixture of betel leaves and betel nut, garlands of flowers, and perfumed ointments, and, showing her skill in arts, should entertain him with a long conversation. She should also give him some loving presents, and make an exchange of her own things with his, and at the same time should show him her skill in sexual enjoyment. When a courtesan is thus united with her lover she should always delight him by affectionate gifts, by conversation, and by the application of tender means of enjoyment.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER II.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF LIVING LIKE A WIFE.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan is living as a wife with her lover, she should behave like a chaste woman, and do everything to his satisfaction. Her duty in this respect, in short, is, that she should give him pleasure, but should not become attached to him, though behaving as if she were really attached.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now the following is the manner in which she is to conduct herself, so as to accomplish the above mentioned purpose. She should have a mother dependent on her, one who should be represented as very harsh, and who looked upon money as her chief object in life. In the event of there being no mother, then an old and confidential nurse should play the same role. The mother or nurse, on their part, should appear to be displeased with the lover, and forcibly take her away from him. The woman herself should always show pretended anger, dejection, fear, and shame on this account, but should not disobey the mother or nurse at any time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>She should make out to the mother or nurse that the man is suffering from bad health, and making this a pretext for going to see him, she should go on that account. She is, moreover, to do the following things for the purpose of gaining the man's favour, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Sending her female attendant to bring the flowers used by him on the previous day, in order that she may use them herself as a mark of affection, also asking for the mixture of betel nut and leaves that have remained uneaten by him; expressing wonder at his knowledge of sexual intercourse, and the several means of enjoyment used by him; learning from him the sixty-four kinds of pleasure mentioned by Babhravya; continually practising the ways of enjoyment as taught by him, and according to his liking; keeping his secrets; telling him<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> her own desires and secrets; concealing her anger; never neglecting him on the bed when he turns his face towards her; touching any parts of his body according to his wish; kissing and embracing him when he is asleep; looking at him with apparent anxiety when he is wrapt in thought, or thinking of some other subject than herself; showing neither complete shamelessness, nor excessive bashfulness when he meets her, or sees her standing on the terrace of her house from the public road; hating his enemies; loving those who are dear to him; showing a liking for that which he likes; being in high or low spirits according to the state that he is in himself; expressing a curiosity to see his wives; not continuing her anger for a long time; suspecting even the marks and wounds made by herself with her nails and teeth on his body to have been made by some other woman; keeping her love for him unexpressed by words, but showing it by deeds, and signs, and hints; remaining silent when he is asleep, intoxicated, or sick; being very attentive when he describes his good actions, and reciting them afterwards to his praise and benefit; giving witty replies to him if he be sufficiently attached to her; listening to all his stories, except those that relate to her rivals; expressing feelings of dejection and sorrow if he sighs, yawns, or falls down; pronouncing the words &quot;live long&quot; when he sneezes; pretending to be ill, or to have the desire of pregnancy, when she feels dejected; abstaining from praising the good qualities of any body else, and from censuring those who possess the same faults as her own man: wearing anything that may have been given to her by him; abstaining from putting on her ornaments, and from taking food when he is in pain, sick, low-spirited, or suffering from misfortune, and condoling and lamenting with him over the same; wishing to accompany him if he happens to leave the country himself or if he be banished from it by the King; expressing a desire not to live after him; telling him that the whole object and desire of her life was to be united with him; offering previously promised sacrifices to the Deity when he acquires wealth, or has some desire fulfilled, or when he has recovered from some illness or disease; putting on ornaments every day; not acting too freely with him; reciting his name and the name of his family in her songs; placing<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> his hand on her loins, bosom and forehead, and falling asleep after feeling the pleasure of his touch; sitting on his lap and falling asleep there; wishing to have a child by him; desiring not to live longer than he does; abstaining from revealing his secrets to others; dissuading him from vows and fasts by saying &quot;let the sin fall upon me;&quot; keeping vows and fasts along with him when it is impossible to change his mind on the subject; telling him that vows and fasts are difficult to be observed, even by herself, when she has any dispute with him about them; looking on her own wealth and his without any distinction; abstaining from going to public assemblies without him, and accompanying him when he desires her to do so; taking delight in using things previously used by him, and in eating food that he has left uneaten; venerating his family, his disposition, his skill in the arts, his learning, his caste, his complexion, his native country, his friends, his good qualities, his age, and his sweet temper; asking him to sing, and to do other such like things, if able to do them; going to him without paying any regard to fear, to cold, to heat, or to rain; saying with regard to the next world that he should be her lover even there; adapting her tastes, disposition and actions to his liking; abstaining from sorcery; disputing continually with her mother on the subject of going to him, and, when forcibly taken by her mother to some other place, expressing her desire to die by taking poison, by starving herself to death, by stabbing herself with some weapon, or by hanging herself; and lastly assuring the man of her constancy and love by means of her agents, and receiving money herself, but abstaining from any dispute with her mother with regard to pecuniary matters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When the man sets out on a journey, she should make him swear that he will return quickly, and in his absence should put aside her vows of worshipping the Deity, and should wear no ornaments except those that are lucky. If the time fixed for his return has passed, she should endeavour to ascertain the real time of his return from omens, from the reports of the people, and from the positions of the planets, the moon and the stars. On occasions of amusement, and of auspicious dreams, she should say &quot;Let me be soon united to him.&quot; <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002534\">If</$link>, moreover, she feels melancholy, or sees any inauspicious omen, she should perform some rite to appease the Deity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When the man does return home she should worship the God Kama (<i>i.e.</i>, the Indian Cupid), and offer oblations to other Deities, and having caused a pot filled with water to be brought by her friends, she should perform the worship in honour of the crow who eats the offerings which we make to the manes of deceased relations. After the first visit is over she should ask her lover also to perform certain rites, and this he will do if he is sufficiently attached to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now a man is said to be sufficiently attached to a woman when his love is disinterested; when he has the same object in view as his beloved one; when he is quite free from any suspicions on her account; and when he is indifferent to money with regard to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Such is the manner of a courtesan living with a man like a wife, and set forth here for the sake of guidance from the rules of Dattaka. What is not laid down here should be practised according to the custom of the people, and the nature of each individual man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also two verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;The extent of the love of women is not known, even to those who are the objects of their affection, on account of its <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002536\">subtlety</$link>, and on account of the avarice, and natural intelligence of womankind.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;Women are hardly ever known in their true light, though they may love men, or become indifferent towards them; may give them delight, or abandon them; or may extract from them all the wealth that they may possess.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER III.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF THE MEANS OF GETTING MONEY. OF THE SIGNS OF THE CHANGE OF A LOVER'S FEELINGS, AND OF THE WAY TO GET RID OF HIM.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Money is got out of a lover in two ways, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>By natural or lawful means, and by artifices. Old authors are of opinion that when a courtesan can get as much money as she wants from her lover, she should not make use of artifice. But Vatsyayana lays down that though she may get some money from him by natural means, yet when she makes use of artifice he gives her doubly more, and therefore artifice should be resorted to for the purpose of extorting money from him at all events.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now the artifices to be used for getting money from her lover are as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>1st. Taking money from him on different occasions, for the purpose of purchasing various articles, such as ornaments, food, drink, flowers, perfumes and cloths, and either not buying them, or getting from him more than their cost.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>2nd. Praising his intelligence to his face.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>3rd. Pretending to be obliged to make gifts on occasion of festivals connected with vows, trees, gardens, temples, or tanks.<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002424\">[75]</$link></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>4th. Pretending that at the time of going to his house, her jewels have been stolen either by the King's guards, or by robbers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>5th. Alleging that her property has been destroyed by<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> fire, by the falling of her house, or by the carelessness of her servants.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>6th. Pretending to have lost the ornaments of her lover along with her own.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>7th. Causing him to hear through other people of the expenses incurred by her in coming to see him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>8th. Contracting debts for the sake of her lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>9th. Disputing with her mother on account of some expense incurred by her for her lover, and which was not approved of by her mother.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>10th. Not going to parties and festivities in the houses of her friends for the want of presents to make to them, she having previously informed her lover of the valuable presents given to her by these very friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>11th. Not performing certain festive rites under the pretence that she has no money to perform them with.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>12th. Engaging artists to do something for her lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>13th. Entertaining physicians and ministers for the purpose of attaining some object.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>14th. Assisting friends and benefactors both on festive occasions, and in misfortune.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>15th. Performing household rites.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>16th. Having to pay the expenses of the ceremony of marriage of the son of a female friend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>17th. Having to satisfy curious wishes during her state of pregnancy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>18th. Pretending to be ill, and charging her cost of treatment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>19th. Having to remove the troubles of a friend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>20th. Selling some of her ornaments, so as to give her lover a present.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>21st. Pretending to sell some of her ornaments, furniture, or cooking utensils to a trader, who has been already tutored how to behave in the matter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>22nd. Having to buy cooking utensils of greater value than those of other people, so that they might be more easily distinguished, and not changed for others of an inferior description.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>23rd. Remembering the former favours of her lover, and<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> causing them always to be spoken of by her friends and followers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>24th. Informing her lover of the great gains of other courtezans.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>25th. Describing before them, and in the presence of her lover, her own great gains, and making them out to be greater even than theirs, though such may not have been really the case.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>26th. Openly opposing her mother when she endeavours to persuade her to take up with men with whom she has been formerly acquainted, on account of the great gains to be got from them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>27th. Lastly, pointing out to her lover the liberality of his rivals.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the ways and means of getting money.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A woman should always know the state of the mind, of the feelings, and of the disposition of her lover towards her, from the changes of his temper, his manner, and the colour of his face.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The behaviour of a waning lover is as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>1st. He gives the woman either less than is wanted, or something else than that which is asked for.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>2nd. He keeps her in hopes by promises.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>3rd. He pretends to do one thing, and does something else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>4th. He does not fulfil her desires.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>5th. He forgets his promises, or does something else than that which he has promised.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>6th. He speaks with his own servants in a mysterious way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>7th. He sleeps in some other house under the pretence of having to do something for a friend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>8th. Lastly, he speaks in private with the attendants of a woman with whom he was formerly acquainted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now when a courtesan finds that her lover's disposition towards her is changing, she should get possession of all his best things before he becomes aware of her intentions, and allow a supposed creditor to take them away forcibly from her in satisfaction of some pretended debt. After this, if the lover is rich, and has always behaved well towards her, she should<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> ever treat him with respect; but if he is poor and destitute, she should get rid of him as if she had never been acquainted with him in any way before.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The means of getting rid of a lover are as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>1st. Describing the habits and vices of the lover as disagreeable and censurable, with the sneer of the lip, and the stamp of the foot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>2nd. Speaking on a subject with which he is not acquainted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>3rd. Showing no admiration for his learning, and passing a censure upon it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>4th. Putting down his pride.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>5th. Seeking the company of men who are superior to him in learning and wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>6th. Showing a disregard for him on all occasions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>7th. Censuring men possessed of the same faults as her lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>8th. Expressing dissatisfaction at the ways and means of enjoyment used by him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>9th. Not giving him her mouth to kiss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>10th. Refusing access to her Jaghana, <i>i.e.</i>, the part of the body between the navel and the thighs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>11th. Showing a dislike for the wounds made by his nails and teeth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>12th. Not pressing close up against him at the time when he embraces her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>13th. Keeping her limbs without movement at the time of congress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>14th. Desiring him to employ her when he is fatigued.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>15th. Laughing at his attachment to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>16th. Not responding to his embraces.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>17th. Turning away from him when he begins to embrace her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>18th. Pretending to be sleepy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>19th. Going out visiting, or into company, when she perceives his desire to enjoy her during the day time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>20th. Mis-constructing his words.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>21st. Laughing without any joke, or at the time of any joke made by him, laughing under some pretence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>22nd. Looking with side glances at her own attendants, and clapping her hands when he says anything.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>23rd. Interrupting him in the middle of his stories, and beginning to tell other stories herself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>24th. Reciting his faults and his vices, and declaring them to be incurable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>25th. Saying words to her female attendants calculated to cut the heart of her lover to the quick.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>26th. Taking care not to look at him when he comes to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>27th. Asking him what cannot be granted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>28th. And, after all, finally dismissing him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also two verses on this subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;The duty of a courtesan consists in forming connections with suitable men after due and full consideration, and attaching the person with whom she is united to herself; in obtaining wealth from the person who is attached to her, and then dismissing him after she has taken away all his possessions.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;A courtesan leading in this manner the life of a wife is not troubled with too many lovers, and yet obtains abundance of wealth.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER IV.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>ABOUT RE-UNION WITH A FORMER LOVER.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan abandons her present lover after all his wealth is exhausted, she may then consider about her re-union with a former lover. But she should return to him only if he has acquired fresh wealth, or is still wealthy, and if he is still attached to her. And if this man be living at the time with some other women she should consider well before she acts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now such a man can only be in one of the six following conditions, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>1st. He may have left the first woman of his own accord, and may even have left another woman since then.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>2nd. He may have been driven away from both women.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>3rd. He may have left the one woman of his own accord, and be living with another woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>5th. He may have been driven away from the one woman, and left the other of his own accord.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>6th. He may have been driven away by the one woman, and may be living with another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(1). Now if the man has left both women of his own accord, he should not be resorted to, on account of the fickleness of his mind, and his indifference to the excellencies of both of them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(2). As regards the man who may have been driven away from both women, if he has been driven away from the last one because the woman could get more money from some other man, then he should be resorted to, for if attached to the first woman he would give her more money, through vanity and emulation to spite the other woman. But if he has been driven away by the woman on account of his poverty, or stinginess, he should not then be resorted to.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>(3). In the case of the man who may have left the one woman of his own accord, and been driven away by the other, if he agrees to return to the former and give her plenty of money beforehand, then he should be resorted to.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(4). In the case of the man who may have left the one woman of his own accord, and be living with another woman, the former (wishing to take up with him again) should first ascertain if he left her in the first instance in the hope of finding some particular excellence in the other woman, and that not having found any such excellence, he was willing to come back to her, and to give her much money on account of his conduct, and on account of his affection still existing for her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Or, whether, having discovered many faults in the other woman, he would now see even more excellences in herself than actually exist, and would be prepared to give her much money for these qualities.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Or, lastly, to consider whether he was a weak man, or a man fond of enjoying many women, or one who liked a poor woman, or one who never did anything for the woman that he was with. After maturely considering all these things, she should resort to him or not, according to circumstances.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(5). As regards the man who may have been driven away from the one woman, and left the other of his own accord, the former woman (wishing to re-unite with him) should first ascertain whether he still has any affection for her, and would consequently spend much money upon her; or whether, being attached to her excellent qualities, he did not take delight in any other women; or whether, being driven away from her formerly before completely satisfying his sexual desires, he wished to get back to her, so as to be revenged for the injury done to him; or whether he wished to create confidence in her mind, and then take back from her the wealth which she formerly took from him, and finally destroy her; or, lastly, whether he wished first to separate her from her present lover, and then to break away from her himself. If, after considering all these things, she is of opinion that his intentions are really pure and honest, she can re-unite herself with him. But if his mind be at all tainted with evil intentions, he should be avoided.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(6). In the case of the man who may have been driven<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> away by one woman, and be living with another, if the man makes overtures in return to the first one, the courtesan should consider well before she acts, and while the other woman is engaged in attracting him to herself, she should try in her turn (through keeping herself behind the scenes) to gain him over, on the grounds of any of the following considerations, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>1st. That he was driven away unjustly and for no proper reason, and now that he has gone to another woman, every effort must be used to bring him back to myself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>2nd. That if he were once to converse with me again, he would break away from the other woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>3rd. That the pride of my present lover would be put down by means of the former one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>4th. That he has become wealthy, has secured a higher position, and holds a place of authority under the King.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>5th. That he is separate from his wife.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>6th. That he is now independent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>7th. That he lives apart from his father, or brother.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>8th. That by making peace with him I shall be able to get hold of a very rich man, who is now prevented from coming to me by my present lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>9th. That as he is not respected by his wife, I shall now be able to separate him from her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>10th. That the friend of this man loves my rival, who hates me cordially; I shall, therefore, by this means separate the friend from his mistress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>11th. And lastly, I shall bring discredit upon him by bringing him back to me, thus showing the fickleness of his mind.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan is resolved to take up again with a former lover, her Pithamurda and other servants should tell him that his former expulsion from the woman's house was caused by the wickedness of her mother; that the woman loved him just as much as ever at that time, but could not help the occurrence on account of her deference to her mother's will; that she hated the union of her present lover, and disliked him excessively. In addition to this, they should create confidence in his mind by speaking to him of her former love for him, and should allude to the mark of that love that<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> she has ever remembered. This mark of her love should be connected with some kind of pleasure that may have been practised by him, such as his way of kissing her, or manner of having connection with her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the ways of bringing about a re-union with a former lover.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a woman has to choose between two lovers, one of whom was formerly united with her, while the other is a stranger, the Acharyas (sages) are of opinion that the first one is preferable, because his disposition and character being already known by previous careful observation, he can be easily pleased and satisfied; but Vatsyayana thinks that a former lover, having already spent a great deal of his wealth, is not able or willing to give much money again, and is not, therefore, to be relied upon so much as a stranger. Particular cases may, however, arise differing from this general rule on account of the different natures of men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;Re-union with a former lover may be desirable so as to separate some particular woman from some particular man, or some particular man from some particular woman, or to have a certain effect upon the present lover.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;When a man is excessively attached to a woman, he is afraid of her coming into contact with other men; he does not then regard or notice her faults; and he gives her much wealth through fear of her leaving him.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;A courtesan should be agreeable to the man who is attached to her, and despise the man who does not care for her. If while she is living with one man a messenger comes to her from some other man, she may either refuse to listen to any negotiations on his part, or appoint a fixed time for him to visit her, but she should not leave the man who may be living with her and who may be attached to her.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;A wise woman should only renew her connection with a former lover if she is satisfied that good fortune, gain, love, and friendship, are likely to be the result of such a re-union.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER V.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF DIFFERENT KINDS OF GAIN.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan is able to realize much money every day, by reason of many customers, she should not confine herself to a single lover; under such circumstances, she should fix her rate for one night, after considering the place, the season, and the condition of the people, and having regard to her own good qualities and good looks, and after comparing her rates with those of other courtesans. She can inform her lovers, and friends, and acquaintances about these charges. If, however, she can obtain a great gain from a single lover, she may resort to him alone, and live with him like a wife.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, the Sages are of opinion that when a courtesan has the chance of an equal gain from two lovers at the same time, a preference should be given to the one who would give her the kind of thing which she wants. But Vatsyayana says that the preference should be given to the one who gives her gold, because it cannot be taken back like some other things, it can be easily received, and is also the means of procuring anything that may be wished for. Of such things as gold, silver, copper, bell metal, iron, pots, furniture, beds, upper garments, under vestments, fragrant substances, vessels made of gourds, ghee, oil, corn, cattle, and other things of a like nature, the first, viz., gold, is superior to all the others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When the same labour is required to gain any two lovers, or when the same kind of thing is to be got from each of them, the choice should be made by the advice of a friend, or it may be made from their personal qualities, or from the signs of good or bad fortune that may be connected with them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When there are two lovers, one of whom is attached to the courtesan, and the other is simply very generous, the Sages say that the preference should be given to the generous lover, but Vatsyayana is of opinion that the one who is really attached<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> to the courtesan should be preferred, because he can be made to be generous, even as a miser gives money if he becomes fond of a woman, but a man who is simply generous cannot be made to love with real attachment. But among those who are attached to her, if there is one who is poor, and one who is rich, the preference is of course to be given to the latter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When there are two lovers, one of whom is generous, and the other ready to do any service for the courtesan, some Sages say that the one who is ready to do the service should be preferred, but Vatsyayana is of opinion that a man who does a service thinks that he has gained his object when he has done something once, but a generous man does not care for what he has given before. Even here the choice should be guided by the likelihood of the future good to be derived from her union with either of them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When one of the two lovers is grateful, and the other liberal, some Sages say that the liberal one should be preferred, but Vatsyayana is of opinion that the former should be chosen, because liberal men are generally haughty, plain spoken, and wanting in consideration towards others. Even though these liberal men have been on friendly terms for a long time, yet if they see any fault in the courtesan, or are told lies about her by some other women, they do not care for past services, but leave abruptly. On the other hand the grateful man does not at once break off from her, on account of a regard for the pains she may have taken to please him. In this case also the choice is to be guided with respect to what may happen in future.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When an occasion for complying with the request of a friend, and a chance of getting money come together, the Sages say that the chance of getting money should be preferred. But Vatsyayana thinks that the money can be obtained to-morrow as well as to-day, but if the request of a friend be not at once complied with, he may become disaffected. Even here, in making the choice, regard must be paid to future good fortune.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>On such an occasion, however, the courtesan might pacify her friend by pretending to have some work to do, and telling him that his request will be complied with next day, and in this way secure the chance of getting the money that has been offered her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>When the chance of getting money, and the chance of avoiding some disaster come at the same time, the Sages are of opinion that the chance of getting money should be preferred, but Vatsyayana says that money has only a limited importance, while a disaster that is once averted may never occur again. Here, however, the choice should be guided by the greatness or smallness of the disaster.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The gains of the wealthiest and best kind of courtesans are to be spent as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Building temples, tanks, and gardens; giving a thousand cows to different Brahmans; carrying on the worship of the Gods, and celebrating festivals in their honour; and, lastly, performing such vows as may be within their means.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The gains of other courtesans are to be spent as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Having a white dress to wear every day; getting sufficient food and drink to satisfy hunger and thirst; eating daily a perfumed Tambula, <i>i.e.</i>, a mixture of betel nut and betel leaves; and wearing ornaments gilt with gold. The Sages say that these represent the gains of all the middle and lower classes of courtesans, but Vatsyayana is of opinion that their gains cannot be calculated, or fixed in any way, as these depend on the influence of the place, the customs of the people, their own appearance, and many other things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan wants to keep some particular man from some other woman; or wants to get him away from some woman to whom he may be attached; or to deprive some woman of the gains realized by her from him; or if she thinks that she would raise her position; or enjoy some great good fortune; or become desirable to all men by uniting herself with this man; or if she wishes to get his assistance in averting some misfortune; or is really attached to him and loves him; or wishes to injure somebody through his means; or has regard to some former favour conferred upon her by him; or wishes to be united with him merely from desire; or any of the above reasons, she should agree to take from him only a small sum of money in a friendly way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan intends to abandon a particular lover, and take up with another one; or when she has reason to believe that her lover will shortly leave her, and return to his wives; or that having squandered all his money, and became<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> penniless, his guardian, or master, or father would come and take him away; or that her lover is about to lose his position, or lastly, that he is of a very fickle mind, she should, under any of these circumstances, endeavour to get as much money as she can from him as soon as possible.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>On the other hand, when the courtesan thinks that her lover is about to receive valuable presents; or get a place of authority from the King; or be near the time of inheriting a fortune; or that his ship would soon arrive laden with merchandise; or that he has large stocks of corn and other commodities; or that if anything was done for him it would not be done in vain; or that he is always true to his word; then should she have regard to her future welfare, and live with the man like a wife.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;In considering her present gains, and her future welfare, a courtesan should avoid such persons as have gained their means of subsistence with very great difficulty, as also those who have become selfish and hard-hearted by becoming the favourites of Kings.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;She should make every endeavour to unite herself with prosperous <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002538\">and</$link> well-to-do people, and with those whom it is dangerous to avoid, or to slight in any way. Even at some cost to herself she should become acquainted with energetic and liberal-minded men, who when pleased would give her a large sum of money, even for very little service, or for some small thing.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER VI.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF GAINS AND LOSSES; ATTENDANT GAINS AND LOSSES; AND DOUBTS; AS ALSO OF THE DIFFERENT KINDS OF COURTESANS.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>It sometimes happens that while gains are being sought for, or expected to be realised, that losses only are the result of our efforts, the causes of these losses are:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"1\">Weakness of intellect.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"2\">Excessive love.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"3\">Excessive pride.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"4\">Excessive self conceit</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"5\">Excessive simplicity.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"6\">Excessive confidence.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"7\">Excessive anger.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"8\">Carlessness.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"9\">Recklessness.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"10\">Influence of evil genius.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"11\">Accidental circumstances.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The results of these losses are:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"1\">Expense incurred without any result.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"2\">Destruction of future good fortune.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"3\">Stoppage of gains about to be realized.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"4\">Loss of what is already obtained.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"5\">Acquisition of a sour temper.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"6\">Becoming unaimiable to every body.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"7\">Injury to health.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"8\">Loss of hair and other accidents.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now gain is of three kinds, viz.: gain of wealth, gain of religious merit, and gain of pleasure; and similarly, loss is of three kinds, viz.: loss of wealth, loss of religious merit, and loss of pleasure. At the time when gains are sought for, if other gains come along with them, these are called attendant gains. When gain is uncertain, the doubt of its being a gain<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> is called a simple doubt. When there is a doubt whether either of two things will happen or not, it is called a mixed doubt. If while one thing is being done two results take place, it is called a combination of two results, and if several results follow from the same action, it is called a combination of results on every side.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>We shall now give examples of the above.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>As already stated, gain is of three kinds, and loss, which is opposed to gain, is also of three kinds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). When by living with a great man a courtesan acquires present wealth, and in addition to this becomes acquainted with other people, and thus obtains a chance of future fortune, and an accession of wealth, and becomes desirable to all, this is called a gain of wealth attended by other gain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). When by living with a man a courtesan simply gets money, this is called a gain of wealth not attended by any other gain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). When a courtesan receives money from other people besides her lover, the results are: the chance of the loss of future good from her present lover; the chance of disaffection of a man securely attached to her; the hatred of all; and the chance of a union with some low person, tending to destroy her future good. This gain is called a gain of wealth attended by losses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). When a courtesan, at her own expense, and without any results in the shape of gain, has connected with a great man, or an avaricious minister, for the sake of diverting some misfortune, or removing some cause that may be threatening the destruction of a great gain, this loss is said to be a loss of wealth attended by gains of the future good which it may bring about.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(e). When a courtesan is kind, even at her own expense, to a man who is very stingy, or to a man proud of his looks, or to an ungrateful man skilled in gaining the heart of others, without any good resulting from these connections to her in the end, this loss is called a loss of wealth not attended by any gain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(f). When a courtesan is kind to any such man as des<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>cribed above, but who in addition are favourites of the King, and moreover cruel and powerful, without any good result in the end, and with a chance of her being turned away at any moment, this loss is called a loss of wealth attended by other losses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In this way gains and losses, and attendant gains and losses in religious merit and pleasures may become known to the reader, and combinations of all of them may also be made.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the remarks on gains and losses, and attendant gains and losses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the next place we come to doubts, which are again of three kinds, viz.: doubts about wealth, doubts about religious merit, and doubts about pleasures.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The following are examples.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). When a courtesan is not certain how much a man may give her, or spend upon her, this is called a doubt about wealth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). When a courtesan feels doubtful whether she is right in entirely abandoning a lover from whom she is unable to get money, she having taken all his wealth from him in the first instance, this doubt is called a doubt about religious merit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). When a courtesan is unable to get hold of a lover to her liking, and is uncertain whether she will derive any pleasure from a person surrounded by his family, or from a low person, this is called a doubt about pleasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). When a courtesan is uncertain whether some powerful but low principled fellow would cause loss to her on account of her not being civil to him, this is called a doubt about the loss of wealth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(e). When a courtesan feels doubtful whether she would lose religious merit by abandoning a man who is attached to her without giving him the slightest favour, and thereby causing him unhappiness in this world and the next,<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002428\">[76]</$link> this doubt is called a doubt about the loss of a religious merit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(f). When a courtesan is uncertain as to whether she might<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> create disaffection by speaking out, and revealing her love and thus not get her desire satisfied, this is called a doubt about the loss of pleasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the remarks on doubts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"center\"><i>Mixed Doubts</i>.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). The intercourse or connection with a stranger, whose disposition is unknown, and who may have been introduced by a lover, or by one who possessed authority, may be productive either of gain or loss, and therefore this is called a mixed doubt about the gain and loss of wealth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). When a courtesan is requested by a friend, or is impelled by pity to have intercourse with a learned Brahman, a religious student, a sacrificer, a devotee, or an ascetic who may have all fallen in love with her, and who may be consequently at the point of death, by doing this she might either gain or lose religious merit, and therefore this is called a mixed doubt about the gain and loss of religious merit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). If a courtesan relies solely upon the report of other people (<i>i.e.</i>, hearsay) about a man, and goes to him without ascertaining herself whether he possesses good qualities or not, she may either gain or lose pleasure in proportion as he may be good or bad, and therefore this is called a mixed doubt about the gain and loss of pleasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Uddalika has described the gains and losses on both sides as follows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). If, when living with a lover, a courtesan gets both wealth and pleasure from him, it is called a gain on both sides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). When a courtesan lives with a lover at her own expense without getting any profit out of it, and the lover even takes back from her what he may have formerly given her, it is called a loss on both sides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). When a courtesan is uncertain whether a new acquaintance would become attached to her, and, moreover, if he became attached to her, whether he would give<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> her any thing, it is then called a doubt on both sides about gains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). When a courtesan is uncertain whether a former enemy, if made up by her at her own expense, would do her some injury on account of his grudge against her; or, if becoming attached to her, would take away angrily from her any thing that he may have given to her, this is called a doubt on both sides about loss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Babhravya has described the gains and losses on both sides as follows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). When a courtesan can get money from a man whom she may go to see, and also money from a man whom she may not go to see, this is called a gain on both sides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). When a courtesan has to incur further expense if she goes to see a man, and yet runs the risk of incurring an irremediable loss if she does not go to see him, this is called a loss on both sides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). When a courtesan is uncertain, whether a particular man would give her anything on her going to see him, without incurring expense on her part, or whether on her neglecting him another man would give her something, this is called a doubt on both sides about gain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d.) When a courtesan is uncertain, whether, on going at her own expense to see an old enemy, he would take back from her what he may have given her, or whether by her not going to see him he would cause some disaster to fall upon her, this is called a doubt on both sides about loss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>By combining the above, the following six kinds of mixed results are produced, viz.:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><span class=\"c11\">(a). Gain on one side, and loss on the other.</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(b). Gain on one side, and doubt of gain on the other.</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(c). Gain on one side, and doubt of loss on the other.</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(d). Loss on one side, and doubt of gain on the other.</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(e). Doubt of gain on one side, and doubt of loss on the other.</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(f). Doubt of loss on one side, and loss on the other.</span><br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A courtesan, having considered all the above things, and taken council with her friends, should act so as to acquire gain, the chances of great gain, and the warding off of any<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> great disaster. Religious merit and pleasure should also be formed into separate combinations like those of wealth, and then all should be combined with each other, so as to form new combinations.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a courtesan consorts with men she should cause each of them to give her money as well as pleasure. At particular times, such as the Spring Festivals, etc., she should make her mother announce to the various men, that on a certain day her daughter would remain with the man who would gratify such and such a desire of hers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When young men approach her with delight, she should think of what she may accomplish through them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The combination of gains and losses on all sides are: gain on one side, and loss on all others; loss on one side and gain on all others; gain on all sides, loss on all sides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>A courtesan should also consider doubts about gain and doubts about loss with reference both to wealth, religious merit, and pleasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus ends the consideration of gain, loss, attendant gains, attendant losses, and doubts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The different kinds of courtesans are:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"1\">A bawd.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"2\">A female attendant.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"3\">An unchaste woman.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"4\">A dancing girl.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"5\">A female artisan.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"6\">A woman who has left her family.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"7\">A woman living on her beauty.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\"><li value=\"8\">And, finally, a regular courtesan.</li></ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ul class=\"c4\">\n</ul></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>All the above kinds of courtesans are acquainted with various kinds of men, and should consider the ways of getting money from them, of pleasing them, of separating themselves from them, and of re-uniting with them. They should also take into consideration particular gains and losses, attendant gains and losses, and doubts in accordance with their several conditions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the considerations of courtesans.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also two verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;Men want pleasure, while women want money, and there<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>fore this Part, which treats of the means of gaining wealth, should be studied.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;There are some women who seek for love, and there are others who seek for money; for the former the ways of love are told in previous portions of this work, while the ways of getting money, as practised by courtesans, are described in this Part.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"fm3\"><span class=\"smcap c10\">End of Part VI.</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>PART VII.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2>ABOUT THE MEANS OF ATTRACTING OTHERS TO YOURSELF.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER I.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>ON PERSONAL ADORNMENT; ON SUBJUGATING THE HEARTS OF OTHERS; AND ON TONIC MEDICINES.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a person fails to obtain the object of his desires by any of the ways previously related, he should then have recourse to other ways of attracting others to himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, good looks, good qualities, youth, and liberality are the chief and most natural means of making a person agreeable in the eyes of others. But in the absence of these a man or a woman must have resort to artificial means, or to art, and the following are some recipes that may be found useful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). An ointment made of the tabernamontana coronaria, the costus speciosus or arabicus, and the flacourtia cataphracta, can be used as an unguent of adornment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). If a fine powder is made of the above plants, and applied to the wick of a lamp, which is made to burn with the oil of blue vitrol, the black pigment or lamp black produced therefrom, when applied to the eye-lashes, has the effect of making a person look lovely.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). The oil of the hog weed, the echites putescens, the sarina plant, the yellow amaranth, and the leaf of the nymphæ, if applied to the body, has the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). A black pigment from the same plants produce a similar effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(e). By eating the powder of the nelumbrium speciosum, the blue lotus, and the mesna roxburghii, with ghee and honey, a man becomes lovely in the eyes of others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>(f). The above things, together with the tabernamontana coronaria, and the xanthochymus pictorius, if used as an ointment, produce the same results.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(g). If the bone of a peacock or of an hyena be covered with gold, and tied on the right hand, it makes a man lovely in the eyes of other people.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(h). In the same way, if a bead, made of the seed of the jujube, or of the conch shell, be enchanted by the <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002540\">incantations</$link> mentioned in the Atharvana Veda, or by the incantations of those well skilled in the science of magic, and tied on the hand, it produces the same result as described above.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(i). When a female attendant arrives at the age of puberty, her master should keep her secluded, and when men ardently desire her on account of her seclusion, and on account of the difficulty of approaching her, he should then bestow her hand on such a person as may endow her with wealth and happiness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This is a means of increasing the loveliness of a person in the eyes of others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the same way, when the daughter of a courtesan arrives at the age of puberty, the mother should get together a lot of young men of the same age, disposition, and knowledge as her daughter, and tell them that she would give her in marriage to the person who would give her presents of a particular kind.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>After this the daughter should be kept in seclusion as far as possible, and the mother should give her in marriage to the man who may be ready to give her the presents agreed upon. If the mother is unable to get so much out of the man, she should show some of her own things as having been given to the daughter by the bridegroom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Or, the mother may allow her daughter to be married to the man privately, as if she was ignorant of the whole affair, and then pretending that it has come to her knowledge, she may give her consent to the union.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The daughter, too, should make herself attractive to the sons of wealthy citizens, unknown to her mother, and make them attached to her, and for this purpose should meet them at the time of learning to sing, and in places where<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> music is played, and at the houses of other people, and then request her mother, through a female friend, or servant, to be allowed to unite herself to the man who is most agreeable to her.<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002432\">[77]</$link></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When the daughter of a courtesan is thus given to a man, the ties of marriage should be observed for one year, and after that she may do what she likes. But even after the end of the year, when otherwise engaged, if she should be now and then invited by her first husband to come and see him, she should put aside her present gain, and go to him for the night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Such is the mode of temporary marriage among courtesans, and of increasing their loveliness, and their value in the eyes of others. What has been said about them should also be understood to apply to the daughters of dancing women, whose mothers should give them only to such persons as are likely to become useful to them in various ways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the ways of making oneself lovely in the eyes of others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). If a man, after anointing his lingam with a mixture of the powders of the white thorn apple, the long pepper, and the black pepper, and honey, engages in sexual union with a woman, he makes her subject to his will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). The application of a mixture of the leaf of the plant vatodbhranta, of the flowers thrown on a human corpse when carried out to be burnt, and the powder of the bones of the peacock, and of the jiwanjiva bird, produces the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). The remains of a kite who has died a natural death, ground into powder, and mixed with cowach and honey, has also the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). Anointing oneself with an ointment made of the plant emblica myrabolans has the power of subjecting women to one's will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(e). If a man cuts into small pieces the sprouts of the<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> vajnasunhi plant, and dips them into a mixture of red arsenic and sulphur, and then dries them seven times, and applies this powder mixed with honey to his lingam, he can subjugate a woman to his will directly that he has had sexual union with her, or, if, by burning these very sprouts at night and looking at the smoke, he sees a golden moon behind, he will then be successful with any woman; or if he throws some of the powder of these same sprouts mixed with the excrement of a monkey upon a maiden, she will not be given in marriage to any body else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(f). If pieces of the arris root are dressed with the oil of the mango, and placed for six months in a hole made in the trunk of the sisu tree, and are then taken out and made up into an ointment, and applied to the lingam, this is said to serve as the means of subjugating women.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(g). If the bone of a camel is dipped into the juice of the plant eclipta prostata, and then burnt, and the black pigment produced from its ashes is placed in a box also made of the bone of a camel, and applied together with antimony to the eye lashes with a pencil also made of the bone of a camel, then that pigment is said to be very pure, and wholesome for the eyes, and serves as a means of subjugating others to the person who uses it. The same effect can be produced by black pigment made of the bones of hawks, vultures, and peacocks.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus end the ways of subjugating others to one's own will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now the means of increasing sexual vigour are as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). A man obtains sexual vigour by drinking milk mixed with sugar, the root of the uchchata plant, the piper chaba, and liquorice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). Drinking milk mixed with sugar, and having the testicle of a ram or a goat boiled in it, is also productive of vigour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). The drinking of the juice of the hedysarum gangeticum, the kuili, and the kshirika plant mixed with milk, produces the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). The seed of the long pepper along with the seeds of the sanseviera roxburghiana, and the hedysarum gangeticum<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> plant, all pounded together, and mixed with milk, is productive of a similar result.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(e). According to ancient authors, if a man pounds the seeds or roots of the trapa <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002542\">bispinosa</$link>, the kasurika, the tuscan jasmine, and liquorice, together with the kshirakapoli (a kind of onion), and puts the powder into milk mixed with sugar and ghee, and having boiled the whole mixture on a moderate fire, drinks the paste so formed, he will be able to enjoy innumerable women.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(f). In the same way, if a man mixes rice with the eggs of the sparrow, and having boiled this in milk, adds to it ghee and honey, and drinks as much of it as necessary, this will produce the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(g). If a man takes the outer covering of sesamum seeds, and soaks them with the eggs of sparrows, and then, having boiled them in milk, mixed with sugar and ghee, along with the fruits of the trapa bispinosa and the kasurika plant, and adding to it the flour of wheat and beans, and then drinks this composition, he is said to be able to enjoy many women.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(h). If ghee, honey, sugar, and liquorice in equal quantities, the juice of the fennel plant, and milk are mixed together, this nectar-like composition is said to be holy, and provocative of sexual vigour, a preservative of life, and sweet to the taste.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(i). The drinking of a paste composed of the asparagus racemosus, the shvadaushtra plant, the guduchi plant, the long pepper, and liquorice, boiled in milk, honey, and ghee, in the spring, is said to have the same effect as the above.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(j). Boiling the asparagus racemosus, and the shvadaushtra plant, along with the pounded fruits of the premna spinosa in water, and drinking the same, is said to act in the same way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(k). Drinking boiled ghee, or clarified butter in the morning during the spring season, is said to be beneficial to health and strength, and agreeable to the taste.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(1). If the powder of the seed of the shvadaushtra plant and the flower of barley are mixed together in equal parts, and a portion of it, <i>i.e.</i>, two palas in weight, is eaten every morning on getting up, it has the same effect as the preceding recipe.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also verses on the subject as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>&quot;The means<a></a><$link class=\"fnanchor pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002436\">[78]</$link> of producing love and sexual vigour should be learnt from the science of medicine, from the Vedas, from those who are learned in the arts of magic, and from confidential relatives. No means should be tried which are doubtful in their effects, which are likely to cause injury to the body, which involve the death of animals, and which bring us in contact with impure things. Such means should only be used as are holy, acknowledged to be good, and approved of by Brahmans, and friends.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CHAPTER II.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h3>OF THE WAYS OF EXCITING DESIRE, AND MISCELLANEOUS EXPERIMENTS, AND RECIPES.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>If a man is unable to satisfy a Hastini, or elephant woman, he should have recourse to various means to excite her passion. At the commencement he should rub her yoni with his hand or fingers, and not begin to have intercourse with her until she becomes excited, or experiences pleasure. This is one way of exciting a woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Or, he may make use of certain Apadravyas, or things which are put on or around the lingam to supplement its length or its thickness, so as to fit it to the yoni. In the opinion of Babhravya, these Apadravyas should be made of gold, silver, copper, iron, ivory, buffalo's horn, various kinds of wood, tin or lead, and should be soft, cool, provocative of sexual vigour, and well fitted to serve the intended purpose. Vatsyayana, however, says that they may be made according to the natural liking of each individual.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The following are the different kinds of Apadravyas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"1\">&quot;The armlet&quot; (Valaya) should <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002544\">be</$link> of the same size as the lingam, and should have its outer surface made rough with globules.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"2\">&quot;The couple&quot; (Sanghati) is formed of two armlets.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"3\">&quot;The bracelet&quot; (Chudaka) is made by joining three or more armlets, until they come up to the required length of the lingam.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"4\">&quot;The single bracelet&quot; is formed by wrapping a single wire around the lingam, according to its dimensions.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol><li value=\"5\">The Kantuka or Jalaka is a tube open at both ends, with a hole through it, outwardly rough and studded with soft<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> globules, and made to fit the side of the yoni, and tied to the waist.</li></ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><ol>\n</ol></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When such a thing cannot be obtained, then a tube made of the wood apple, or tubular stalk of the bottle gourd, or a reed made soft with oil and extracts of plants, and tied to the waist with strings, may be made use of, as also a row of soft pieces of wood tied together.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The above are the things that can be used in connection with or in the place of the lingam.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The people of the southern countries think that true sexual pleasure cannot be obtained without perforating the lingam, and they therefore cause it to be pierced like the lobes of the ears of an infant pierced for earrings.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, when a young man perforates his lingam he should pierce it with a sharp instrument, and then stand in water so long as the blood continues to flow. At night he should engage in sexual intercourse, even with vigour, so as to clean the hole. After this he should continue to wash the hole with decoctions, and increase the size by putting into it small pieces of cane, and the wrightia antidysenterica, and thus gradually enlarging the orifice. It may also be washed with liquorice mixed with honey, and the size of the hole increased by the fruit stalks of the sima-patra plant. The hole should be annointed with a small quantity of oil.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In the hole made in the lingam a man may put Apadravyas of various forms, such as the &quot;round,&quot; the &quot;round on one side,&quot; the &quot;wooden mortar,&quot; the &quot;flower,&quot; the &quot;armlet,&quot; the &quot;bone of the heron,&quot; the &quot;goad of the elephant,&quot; the &quot;collection of eight balls,&quot; the &quot;lock of hair,&quot; the &quot;place where four roads meet,&quot; and other things named according to their forms and means of using them. All these Apadravyas should be rough on the outside according to their requirements.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The ways of enlarging the lingam must be now related.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>When a man wishes to enlarge his lingam, he should rub it with the bristles of certain insects that live in trees, and then, after rubbing it for ten nights with oils, he should again rub it with the bristles as before. By continuing to do this a swelling will be gradually produced in the lingam,<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> and he should then lie on a cot, and cause his lingam to hang down through a hole in the cot. After this he should take away all the pain from the swelling by using cool concoctions. The swelling, which is called &quot;Suka,&quot; and is often brought about among the people of the Dravida country, lasts for life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>If the lingam is rubbed with the following things, viz., the plant physalis flexuosa, the shavara-kandaka plant, the jalasuka plant, the fruit of the egg plant, the butter of a she buffalo, the hastri-charma plant, and the juice of the vajra-rasa plant, a swelling lasting for one month will be produced.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>By rubbing it with oil boiled in the concoctions of the above things, the same effect will be produced, but lasting for six months.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The enlargement of the lingam is also effected by rubbing it or moistening it with oil boiled on a moderate fire along with the seeds of the <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002546\">pomegranate</$link>, and the cucumber, the juices of the valuka plant, the hasti-charma plant, and the egg-plant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>In addition to the above, other means may be learnt from experienced and confidential persons.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>The miscellaneous experiments and recipes are as follows:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(a). If a man mixes the powder of the milk hedge plant, and the kantaka plant with the excrement of a monkey, and the powdered root of the lanjalalika plant, and throws this mixture on a woman, she will not love any body else afterwards.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(b). If a man thickens the juice of the fruits of the cassia fistula, and the eugenia jambolana by mixing them with the powder of the soma plant, the vernonia anthelmintica, the eclipta prostata, and the lohopa-jihirka, and applies this composition to the yoni of a woman, and then has sexual intercourse with her, his love for her will be destroyed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(c). The same effect is produced if a man has connection with a woman who has bathed in the butter-milk of a she-buffalo mixed with the powders of the gopalika plant, the banu-padika plant, and the yellow amaranth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(d). An ointment made of the flowers of the nauclea cadamba, the hog plum, and the eugenia jambolana, and used by a woman, causes her to be disliked by her husband.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a>(e). Garlands made of the above flowers, when worn by the woman, produce the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(f). An ointment made of the fruit of the asteracantha longifolia (kokilaksha) will contract the yoni of a Hastini or elephant woman, and this contraction lasts for one night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(g). An ointment made by pounding the roots of the nelumbrium speciosum, and of the blue lotus, and the powder of the plant physalis flexuosa mixed with ghee and honey, will enlarge the yoni of the Mrigi or deer woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(h). An ointment made of the fruit of the emblica myrabolans soaked in the milky juice of the milk hedge plant, of the soma plant, the calotropis gigantea, and the juice of the fruit of the vernonia anthelmintica, will make the hair white.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(i). The juice of the roots of the madayantaka plant, the yellow amaranth, the anjanika plant, the clitoria ternateea, and the shlakshnaparni plant, used as a lotion, will make the hair grow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(j). An ointment made by boiling the above roots in oil, and rubbed in, will make the hair black, and will also gradually restore hair that has fallen off.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(k) If lac is saturated seven times in the sweat of the testicle of a white horse, and applied to a red lip, the lip will become white.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(l). The colour of the lips can be regained by means of the madayantika and other plants mentioned above under (i).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(m). A woman who hears a man playing on a reed pipe which has been dressed with the juices of the bahupadika plant, the tabernamontana coronaria, the costus speciosus or arabicus, the pinus deodora, the euphorbia antiquorum, the vajra and the kantaka plant, becomes his slave.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(n). If food be mixed with the fruit of the thorn apple (Dathura) it causes intoxication.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(o). If water be mixed with oil and the ashes of any kind of grass except the kusha grass, it becomes the colour of milk.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(p). If yellow myrabolans, the hog plum, the shrawana plant, and the priyangu plant be all pounded together, and applied to iron pots, these pots become red.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(q). If a lamp, trimmed with oil extracted from the shrawana and priyangn plants, its wick being made of cloth and the slough<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> of the skins of snakes, is lighted, and long pieces of wood placed near it, those pieces of wood will resemble so many snakes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(r). Drinking the milk of a white cow who has a white calf at her feet is auspicious, produces fame, and preserves life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>(s). The blessings of venerable Brahmans, well propitiated, have the same effect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also some verses in conclusion:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;Thus have I written in a few words the 'Science of love,' after reading the texts of ancient authors, and following the ways of enjoyment mentioned in them.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;He who is acquainted with the true principles of this science pays regard to Dharma, Artha, Kama, and to his own experiences, as well as to the teachings of others, and does not act simply on the dictates of his own desire. As for the errors in the science of love which I have mentioned in this work, on my own authority as an author, I have, immediately after mentioning them, carefully censured and prohibited them.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;An act is never looked upon with indulgence for the simple reason that it is authorised by the science, because it ought to be remembered that it is the intention of the science, that the rules which it contains should only be acted upon in particular cases. After reading and considering the works of Babhravya and other ancient authors, and thinking over the meaning of the rules given by them, the Kama Sutra was composed, according to the precepts of Holy Writ, for the benefit of the world, by Vatsyayana, while leading the life of a religious student, and wholly engaged in the contemplation of the Deity.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;This work is not intended to be used merely as an instrument for satisfying our desires. A person, acquainted with the true principles of this science, and who preserves his Dharma, Artha, and Kama, and has regard for the practices of the people, is sure to obtain the mastery over his senses.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>&quot;In short, an intelligent and prudent person, attending to Dharma and Artha, and attending to Kama also, without becoming the slave of his passions, obtains success in everything that he may undertake.&quot;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"fm3\"><span class=\"smcap c10\">End of Part VII.</span></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a>CONCLUDING REMARKS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus ends, in seven parts, the Kama Sutra of Vatsyayana, which might otherwise be called a treatise on men and women, their mutual relationship, and connection with each other.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>It is a work that should be studied by all, both old and young; the former will find in it real truths, gathered by experience, and already tested by themselves, while the latter will derive the great advantage of learning things, which some perhaps may otherwise never learn at all, or which they may only learn when it is too late (&quot;too late&quot; those immortal words of Mirabeau) to profit by the learning.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>It can also be fairly commended to the student of social science and of humanity, and above all to the student of those early ideas, which have gradually filtered down through the sands of time, and which seem to prove that the human nature of to-day is much the same as the human nature of the long ago.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>It has been said of Balzac [the great, if not the greatest of French novelists] that he seemed to have inherited a natural and intuitive perception of the feelings of men and women, and has described them with an analysis worthy of a man of science. The author of the present work must also have had a considerable knowledge of the humanities. Many of his remarks are so full of simplicity and truth, that they have stood the test of time, and stand out still as clear and true as when they were first written, some eighteen hundred years ago.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>As a collection of facts, told in plain and simple language, it must be remembered that in those early days there was apparently no idea of embellishing the work, either with a<a class=\"x-ebookmaker-pageno\"></a> literary style, a flow of language, or a quantity of superfluous padding. The author tells the world what he knows in very concise language, without any attempt to produce an interesting story. From his facts how many novels could be written! Indeed much of the matter contained in parts <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001013\"><span class=\"lowercase smcap\">III</span></$link>. <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001118\"><span class=\"lowercase smcap\">IV</span></$link>. <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001174\"><span class=\"lowercase smcap\">V</span></$link>. and <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001553\"><span class=\"lowercase smcap\">VI</span></$link>., has formed the basis of many of the stories and the tales of past centuries.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>There will be found in part <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001931\"><span class=\"lowercase smcap\">VII</span></$link>., some curious recipes. Many of them appear to be as primitive as the book itself, but in later works of the same nature these recipes and prescriptions appear to have increased, both as regards quality and quantity. In the Anunga Runga or &quot;The Stage of Love,&quot; mentioned at page <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000046\">5</$link> of the Preface in Part <span class=\"lowercase smcap\">I.</span>, there are found no less than thirty-three different subjects for which one hundred and thirty recipes and prescriptions are given.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002043": {
