        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000343\"><span class=\"label\">[28]</span></$link> The Vita is supposed to represent somewhat the character of the Parasite of the Greek comedy. It is possible that he was retained about the person of the wealthy and dissipated as a kind of private instructor, as well as an entertaining companion.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000344\"><span class=\"label\">[29]</span></$link> Vidushaka is evidently the buffoon and jester. Wilson says of him that he is the humble companion, not the servant, of a prince or man of rank, and it is a curious peculiarity that he is always a Brahman. He bears more affinity to Sancho Panza, perhaps, than any other character in western fiction, <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002552\">imitating</$link> him in his combination of shrewdness and simplicity, his fondness of good living and his love of ease. In the dramas of intrigue he exhibits some of the talents of Mercury, but with less activity and ingenuity, and occasionally suffers by his interference. According to the technical definition of his attributes he is to excite mirth by being ridiculous in person, age, and attire.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000349\"><span class=\"label\">[30]</span></$link> This means, it is presumed, that the citizen should be acquainted with several languages. The middle part of this paragraph might apply to the Nihilists and Fenians of the day, or to secret societies. It was perhaps a reference to the Thugs.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000354\"><span class=\"label\">[31]</span></$link> This term does not apply to a widow, but to a woman who had probably left her husband, and is living with some other person as a married woman, maritalement, as they say in France.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000355\"><span class=\"label\">[32]</span></$link> Any woman fit to be enjoyed without sin. The object of the enjoyment of women is twofold, viz., pleasure and progeny. Any woman who can be enjoyed without sin for the purpose of accomplishing either the one or the other of these two objects is a Nayika. The fourth kind of Nayika which Vatsya admits further on is neither enjoyed for pleasure or for progeny, but merely for accomplishing some special purpose in hand. The word Nayika is retained as a technical term <a></a><$link class=\"correction pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002554\">throughout</$link>.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000520\"><span class=\"label\">[33]</span></$link> High unions are said to be better than low ones, for in the former it is possible for the male to satisfy his own passion without injuring the female, while in the latter it is difficult for the female to be satisfied by any means.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000537\"><span class=\"label\">[34]</span></$link> The strength of passion with women varies a great deal, some being easily satisfied, and others eager and willing to go on for a long time. To satisfy these last thoroughly a man must have recourse to art. It is certain that a fluid flows from the woman in larger or smaller quantities, but her satisfaction is not complete until she has experienced the &quot;spasme génêsique,&quot; as described in a French work recently published and called &quot;Breviare de l'Amour Experimental par le Dr. Jules Guyot.&quot;</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000542\"><span class=\"label\">[35]</span></$link> This is a long dissertation very common among Sanscrit authors, both when writing and talking socially. They start certain propositions, and then argue for and against them. What it is presumed the author means, is, that though both men and women derive pleasure from the act of coition, the way it is produced is brought about by different means, each individual performing his own work in the matter, irrespective of the other, and each deriving individually their own consciousness of pleasure from the act they perform. There is a difference in the work that each does, and a difference in the consciousness of pleasure that each has, but no difference in the pleasure they feel, for each feels that pleasure to a greater or lesser degree.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
