        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000715\"><span class=\"label\">[37]</span></$link> From this it would appear that in ancient times the breasts of women were not covered, and this is seen in the painting of the Ajunta and other caves, where we find that the breasts of even royal ladies and others are exposed.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002267": {
