        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001526\"><span class=\"label\">[73]</span></$link> It may be noted from the above remarks that eunuchs do not appear to have been employed in the King's harem in those days, though they seem to have been employed for other purposes. See Part II., page <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000546\">43</$link>.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
