            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001686\"><span class=\"label\">[75]</span></$link> On the completion of a vow a festival takes place. Some trees such as the Peepul and Banyan trees, are invested with sacred threads like the Brahman's, and on the occasion of this ceremony a festival is given. In the same way when gardens are made, and tanks or temples built, then also festivals are observed.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001880\"><span class=\"label\">[76]</span></$link> The souls of men who die with their desires unfulfilled are said to go to the world of the Manes, and not direct to the Supreme Spirit.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001951\"><span class=\"label\">[77]</span></$link> It is a custom of the courtesans of Oriental countries to give their daughters temporarily in marriage when they come of age, and after they have received an education in the Kama Sutra and other arts. Full details are given of this at page 76 of &quot;Early Ideas, a group of Hindoo stories, collected and collated by Anaryan. W. H. Allen and Co., London, 1881.&quot;</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000001977\"><span class=\"label\">[78]</span></$link> From the earliest times Oriental authors have occupied themselves about aphrodisiacs. The following note on the subject is taken from page 29 of a translation of the Hindoo Art of Love, otherwise the Anunga Runga, alluded to in the preface of this work, Part I., pages <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000023\">3</$link> and <$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000000046\">5</$link>:—&quot;Most Eastern treatises divide aphrodisiacs into two different kinds: 1., the mechanical or natural, such as scarification, flagellation, etc.; and 2., the medicinal or artificial. To the former belong the application of insects, as is practised by some savage races; and all orientalists will remember the tale of the old Brahman, whose young wife insisted upon his being again stung by a wasp.&quot;</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><h2><a></a><i>Works issued by the Council of the</i> <span class=\"smcap\">Kama Shastra Society</span>.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><i>DETAILED PROSPECTUSES CAN BE HAD.</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>II.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><span class=\"c11\">ANANGA-RANGA,</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(<i>Stage of the Bodiless One</i>)</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">OR THE</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">HINDOO ART OF LOVE,</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">(<i>Ars Amoris Indica</i>,)</span><br>\n<br>\n<span class=\"c11\"><span class=\"smcap\">Translated from the Sanskrit and Annotated by</span></span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">A. F. F. <span class=\"smcap\">AND</span> B. F. R.</span><br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"author\">[<i>Ready.</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>This work may fairly be pronounced unique from the days of Sotades and Ovid to our time. Western authors have treated the subject either jocularly, or with a tendency to hymn the joys of immorality. The Indian author has taken the opposite view, and it is impossible not to admire the delicacy with which he has handled an exceedingly delicate theme.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p>III.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><span class=\"c11\">THE</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">PERFUMED GARDEN,</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">OF THE</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">SHEIK NEFZAOUI,</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\">OR THE</span><br>\n<span class=\"c11\"><i>ARAB ART OF LOVE</i>,</span><br>\n<br>\n<span class=\"c11\"><span class=\"smcap\">XVIth Century.</span></span><br>\n<br>\n<span class=\"c11\"><span class=\"smcap\">Translated from the French Version of the Arabian MS.</span></span><br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"author\">[<i>Ready.</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\"><p><sup><sup>*</sup><sub>*</sub><sup>*</sup></sup>This, the authorized version, is printed in purple and red ink, and ornamented with Arabesque Initial Ornaments.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/ca7bc903db05ca3e/text/000002450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-e24e33 twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-ee4fbb twpub-ca7bc903db05ca3e-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
